{"cursor":"3235","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox company |name = Vernalis plc |logo = |caption = |type = Public\n| traded_as =\n|genre = |fate = |predecessor = |successor = |foundation = 2003 |founder =\n|defunct = |location_city = Winnersh |location_country = United Kingdom\n|location = |locations = |area_served = |key_people = Ian\nGarland (CEO) Peter Fellner (Executive chairman) |industry =\nBiotechnology |products = Frovatriptan, Apokyn |production = |services =\n|revenue = |operating_income = |net_income = |aum = |assets = |equity = |owner =\n|num_employees = 200 |parent = |divisions = |subsid = |homepage =\n[http://www.vernalis.com www.vernalis.com] |footnotes = |intl = }}\n\n'Vernalis plc' is a British based biotech company founded in 2003 by the merger\nof Vernalis Group with British Biotech in a deal valued at Â£90 million. {{cite web\n | year = 2003 url = http://www.advancesinlifescience.com/news_145.htm title =\n | Vernalis agrees Â£91m merger plan with British Biotech work = Advances in Life\n | Science publisher = ALS accessdate = 2003-07-03\n}} The merger allowed British Biotech to ditch its historic but tarnished\nname. {{cite web\n | year = 1998 url = http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm199798/cmselect-\n | /cmsctech/888/88804.htm title = Fifth Report work = Select Committee on\n | Science and Technology publisher = House of Commons accessdate = 2007-11-\n | 28}}\n\nThe company has marketed two drug products; Frovatriptan, to treat\nmigraine, and Apokyn, an apomorphine-based drug for advanced Parkinson's\ndisease. {{cite web\n | year = 2004 url = http://www.fda.gov/Cder/consumerinfo/druginfo/Apokyn.HTM\n | title = Apokyn work = publisher = FDA accessdate = 2004-07-29}} \n\nThe company has a development pipeline focused on CNS disease and oncology, and\ncollaborates with pharmaceutical companies including Novartis, Servier,\nChemGenex and Serono. It is listed on the London Stock Exchange and is a\nconstituent of the